    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely, then peel and finely chop your <strong>garlic </strong>and <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Peel your <strong>potato[es]</strong> and chop them into small, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-goddess-soup-with-garlic-and-pumpkin-seed-chilli-oil/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a lid with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) with the<strong> chilli flakes</strong> and <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until the garlic is golden and fragrant \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic & pumpkin seed chilli oil</strong></p><p>Transfer to a bowl and set aside, reserve the pot</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-goddess-soup-with-garlic-and-pumpkin-seed-chilli-oil/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>leek</strong> and <strong>diced onion</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>miso</strong> in 500ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [800ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.1L] </span><strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>miso stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-goddess-soup-with-garlic-and-pumpkin-seed-chilli-oil/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> chopped ginger </strong>and cook for a further 2-3 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-goddess-soup-with-garlic-and-pumpkin-seed-chilli-oil/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potato</strong> with the <strong>miso</strong> <strong>stock </strong>and a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 15-18 min or until the potato is fork-tender</p><p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>spinach</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-goddess-soup-with-garlic-and-pumpkin-seed-chilli-oil/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potato is fork-tender, stir through your <strong>blanched</strong> <strong>peas </strong>and <strong>spinach </strong>with your <strong>cultured coconut</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 2-3 or until the spinach has wilted</p><p>Once wilted, blitz until smooth with a <strong>(stick) blender</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>green goddess soup</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-goddess-soup-with-garlic-and-pumpkin-seed-chilli-oil/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in <strong>half </strong>and place in the<strong> toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until toasted</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-goddess-soup-with-garlic-and-pumpkin-seed-chilli-oil/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>green goddess soup</strong> in a bowl topped with the <strong>garlic & pumpkin seed chilli oil</strong></p><p>Taste for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed</p><p>Serve the<strong> toasted ciabatta</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: For a little extra indulgence, top the toasted ciabatta with your favourite butter</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
